(14872, 687, 'persons_0_person_description', '<p dir=\"ltr\">Martin Tarr is the Chief Executive Officer of Gulf Business Machines (GBM). As part of his role at GBM, Martin is responsible for leading the overall day-to-day operations of the company from the Dubai headquarters, working closely with the company’s branches based in Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, the UAE, and Pakistan. Martin’s objective is to see GBM continue to successfully work with its customers to cultivate new market opportunities in hardware, software, and services that support the new digital era.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Prior to joining GBM, Martin served as Vice President of IBM’s Global Technology Services for Middle East Africa. This Dubai-based role saw him responsible for IBM’s Managed Services and Strategic Outsourcing Business.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Martin has also served as IBM’s Vice President for Sales in Europe and as Vice President for IBM’s Hardware Business in the same geography.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Martin graduated from the University of London with a B.A. Hons in Classics. A keen sportsman, he has a real passion for football, cricket, and rugby. Originally from the United Kingdom, he currently lives in Dubai with his wife and two children.</p>'),
