(35060, 1146, 'persons_5_person_position', 'General Manager, Qatar '),
(35061, 1146, '_persons_5_person_position', 'field_5b979cce342d9'),
(35062, 1146, 'persons_5_person_description', '<p dir=\"ltr\">Soubhi Chebib, General Manager of GBM Qatar is responsible for all business operations and growth of the company within the country.  Soubhi took on his current role in 2012.  Since then, he has developed GBM Qatar to become the fastest growing operation within the GBM network.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Prior to his current position, Soubhi was GBM’s Regional Director for IBM Systems, where he was instrumental in strengthening the partnership between IBM and GBM to provide leading IT solutions to clients in the region.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">He began his career in France in system design and development, where he developed high security and surveillance systems for France Atomic Research Center and Atlanta Airport in the US.  He Joined IBM in 1982 as a System Engineer in Enterprise Systems and has since held many technical, sales and management positions with IBM World Trade Corporation, IBM Canada and GBM.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Soubhi holds a BSc in Electrical Engineering and a Master’s Degree in Finance and has over 30 years of experience in the IT industry of which 20 years have been in this Region.</p>'),
(35063, 1146, '_persons_5_person_description', 'field_5b979cce343c7'),
(35064, 1146, 'persons_6_person_image', '1130'),
(35065, 1146, '_persons_6_person_image', 'field_5b979cce340fc'),
(35066, 1146, 'persons_6_person_name', 'Wassim Seliman '),
(35067, 1146, '_persons_6_person_name', 'field_5b979cce341ec'),
(35068, 1146, 'persons_6_person_position', 'General Manager, Kuwait '),
(35069, 1146, '_persons_6_person_position', 'field_5b979cce342d9'),
(35070, 1146, 'persons_6_person_description', '<p dir=\"ltr\">Wassim Seliman is the General Manager of GBM Kuwait, a role he has assumed since 2018. Wassim is responsible for maintaining GBM Kuwait’s customer relationships, the growth of the local business as well as the skills development of GBM employees in Kuwait.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Wassim has 28 years’ worth of industry experience and first joined GBM Kuwait in 2003 as an Account Manager. Since then, he has held a number of positions in GBM including Government Market Director.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Wassim graduated with a Bachelor of Science in electronic and communication engineering supported by a London Business School degree in Planning and Strategy. He is also a Baltimore-certified Security PKI Engineer, and has received an ITIL Basic Foundation Certification.</p>'),
(35071, 1146, '_persons_6_person_description', 'field_5b979cce343c7'),
(35072, 1146, 'persons_7_person_image', '1131'),
(35073, 1146, '_persons_7_person_image', 'field_5b979cce340fc'),
(35074, 1146, 'persons_7_person_name', 'Eddy Abboud'),
(35075, 1146, '_persons_7_person_name', 'field_5b979cce341ec'),
(35076, 1146, 'persons_7_person_position', 'General Manager, GBM Oman '),
(35077, 1146, '_persons_7_person_position', 'field_5b979cce342d9'),
(35078, 1146, 'persons_7_person_description', '<p dir=\"ltr\">Eddy Abboud is the general manager of GBM Oman, the Oman-based division of Gulf Business Machines (GBM). In his role, Eddy will be responsible for spearheading GBM Oman’s efforts in support of the Sultanate’s Digital Oman Strategy. He will also oversee client relationships in the Sultanate, supporting public and private sector organizations as they embark on their digital transformation journeys.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">An industry veteran, Eddy’s successful career spans over two decades and several Middle Eastern countries. Having worked with GBM for over 10 years, Eddy began his career in the GBM Dubai office as a Project Manager. His most recent role was based out of the GBM Abu Dhabi office, where he was the Director of Corporate Transformation and Shared Services, a role that saw him manage operations and finance for the branch.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Prior to joining GBM, Eddy held multiple technical and managerial roles in the telecom industry, where he managed Services for internet service providers, telecom operations in various countries, and several projects for Saudi Telecom Company (STC).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Eddy holds a bachelor’s and master’s degree from the American University of Culture &amp; Education in Beirut, Lebanon. He also holds an Executive Education diploma in Leadership from Harvard Business School.</p>'),
(35079, 1146, '_persons_7_person_description', 'field_5b979cce343c7'),
(35080, 1146, 'persons_8_person_image', '1132'),
(35081, 1146, '_persons_8_person_image', 'field_5b979cce340fc'),
(35082, 1146, 'persons_8_person_name', 'Haneef Akhtar'),
(35083, 1146, '_persons_8_person_name', 'field_5b979cce341ec'),
(35084, 1146, 'persons_8_person_position', 'Advisor'),
(35085, 1146, '_persons_8_person_position', 'field_5b979cce342d9'),
(35086, 1146, 'persons_8_person_description', '<p dir=\"ltr\">Haneef Akhtar is the Chief Financial Officer of GBM. He has worked for GBM in Kuwait, Bahrain and now Dubai, and is responsible for the financial well-being of the organization.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Haneef joined IBM India in 1965. Served on assignments in IBM Saudi Arabia. He also worked on assignment in Paris for IBM Middle East &amp; Africa as Financial Operations Manager for Africa. He was involved in the formation of SBM and GBM in 1990, and assumed the post of Finance Manager in GBM.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Haneef holds a MBA degree from Delhi University.</p>'),
(35087, 1146, '_persons_8_person_description', 'field_5b979cce343c7'),
(35088, 1146, 'persons_9_person_image', '1134'),
(35089, 1146, '_persons_9_person_image', 'field_5b979cce340fc'),
(35090, 1146, 'persons_9_person_name', 'Susanne Peter '),
(35091, 1146, '_persons_9_person_name', 'field_5b979cce341ec'),
(35092, 1146, 'persons_9_person_position', 'Chief Financial Officer'),
(35093, 1146, '_persons_9_person_position', 'field_5b979cce342d9'),
(35094, 1146, 'persons_9_person_description', 'Susanne Peter is the Chief Financial Officer of Gulf Business Machines (GBM). She is responsible for the financial strategy and operations of GBM and its branches in the UAE, Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, and Pakistan.                                                                                                                                                Susanne joined GBM in October 2016. Prior to this, she was the Vice President of Finance for IBM Germany, Austria, and Switzerland, where she led the financial operations across all three of these markets. During her 30+ years with IBM, she held various other CFO and VP positions in different business units. Susanne has accumulated a wealth of experience in Growth Markets and Global Headquarter roles and has worked with multiple regions closely, having done stints in Germany, France, the United States, Austria, Ireland, and the Middle East.\r\nSusanne earned her degree in Business Administration from Heilbronn University in Germany.'),
(35095, 1146, '_persons_9_person_description', 'field_5b979cce343c7'),
