(35352, 1147, 'persons_7_person_position', 'General Manager, GBM Oman '),
(35353, 1147, '_persons_7_person_position', 'field_5b979cce342d9'),
(35354, 1147, 'persons_7_person_description', '<p dir=\"ltr\">Eddy Abboud is the general manager of GBM Oman, the Oman-based division of Gulf Business Machines (GBM). In his role, Eddy will be responsible for spearheading GBM Oman’s efforts in support of the Sultanate’s Digital Oman Strategy. He will also oversee client relationships in the Sultanate, supporting public and private sector organizations as they embark on their digital transformation journeys.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">An industry veteran, Eddy’s successful career spans over two decades and several Middle Eastern countries. Having worked with GBM for over 10 years, Eddy began his career in the GBM Dubai office as a Project Manager. His most recent role was based out of the GBM Abu Dhabi office, where he was the Director of Corporate Transformation and Shared Services, a role that saw him manage operations and finance for the branch.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Prior to joining GBM, Eddy held multiple technical and managerial roles in the telecom industry, where he managed Services for internet service providers, telecom operations in various countries, and several projects for Saudi Telecom Company (STC).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Eddy holds a bachelor’s and master’s degree from the American University of Culture &amp; Education in Beirut, Lebanon. He also holds an Executive Education diploma in Leadership from Harvard Business School.</p>'),
